  "prompt": "International awards of Shahrukh Khan?",
  "response": "Shahrukh Khan, often referred to as the \"King of Bollywood\", has received numerous awards and honors throughout his career, including several international accolades. Some of his international awards include:\n\n1. **Legion of Honour (France)** - In 2014, Shahrukh Khan was honored with the prestigious Legion of Honour, which is France's highest civilian award. This recognition was bestowed upon him for his exceptional career and contributions to cultural diversity across the world.\n\n2. **Pyramide con Marni (UNESCO)** - In 2011, Shahrukh Khan received the Pyramide con Marni award from UNESCO for his efforts in supporting children's education and his global humanitarian work.\n\n3. **Asian Awards** - Shahrukh Khan has been honored multiple times at the Asian Awards. Notably, he received the Outstanding Achievement in Cinema award in 2011 and was celebrated for his contribution to Indian cinema and global cultural impacts.\n\n4. **Ordos International Film Festival (China)** - In 2013, Khan was awarded the Best Actor award for his role in the film \"Jab Tak Hai Jaan\" at this film festival in China.\n\n5. **IARA Awards (International Indian Film Academy)** - Shahrukh Khan has also received several awards from IIFA, which recognizes excellence in Indian cinema internationally.\n\nBeyond these, Khan has been celebrated globally including in countries such as Morocco, South Korea, and Germany, recognizing his influence and contribution to cinema and global arts. His international appeal is a testament to his versatility and impact as a performer.",
